================================================================================
THIRD-PARTY DEPENDENCIES
================================================================================

The following notable third-party components are used as dependencies. Full
license texts and pointers are collected in THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md. Versions
reflect the manifests / lockfiles in this repository at time of writing.

--- Attestation (TEE quote verification) -------------------------------------

  dcap-qvl (Rust crate) ....................................... MIT/Apache-2.0
      Intel TDX/SGX DCAP quote verification. Used in caladon-core via the
      pure-Rust `rustcrypto` backend for both the WASM and native targets.
      Pinned at v0.5.2 (Cargo.lock).
      https://github.com/Phala-Network/dcap-qvl

  dcap-qvl-swift (Swift package + bundled Rust core via UniFFI) ........... MIT
      Phala Network's native Swift DCAP verifier (xcframework). A direct
      dependency of the Apple client (SwiftyKit), used for the typed
      Quote/parse/reportData surface. Pinned at v0.5.2 (apple/Package.swift).
      https://github.com/Phala-Network/dcap-qvl-swift

--- Cryptographic primitives -------------------------------------------------

  swift-sodium (Swift binding to libsodium) ............................... ISC
      libsodium primitives (Argon2id, XChaCha20-Poly1305, X25519) for the
      Apple client's seed-identity path. Pinned at >= 0.9.1
      (apple/Package.swift). libsodium itself is ISC-licensed.
      https://github.com/jedisct1/swift-sodium    https://libsodium.org

  PyNaCl (Python binding to libsodium) ................................. Apache-2.0
      XChaCha20-Poly1305 in the gateway (working-memory-key open path).
      Pinned at >= 1.5 (gateway/pyproject.toml). Bundles libsodium (ISC).
      https://github.com/pyca/pynacl

  cryptography (Python / pyca) ............... Apache-2.0 OR BSD-3-Clause
      Cryptographic primitives in the gateway. Pinned at >= 43
      (gateway/pyproject.toml). Statically links OpenSSL (Apache-2.0).
      https://github.com/pyca/cryptography

  Rust crypto crates (caladon-core; RustCrypto ecosystem + dalek) ... MIT/Apache-2.0
      argon2 (0.5.3), hkdf (0.12), sha2 (0.10), chacha20poly1305 (0.10.1),
      ed25519-dalek (2.2.0), x25519-dalek (2.0.1), zeroize (1), base64 (0.22),
      hex (0.4). All dual MIT/Apache-2.0.
      https://github.com/RustCrypto    https://github.com/dalek-cryptography

