EXTERNAL SERVICES (deployed alongside, NOT bundled in this repository)
================================================================================

The following are independently-licensed, separately-deployed services that the
gateway communicates with over the network (e.g. HTTP). Their source is NOT
vendored or redistributed in this repository; they are listed for completeness
and to credit the projects whose interfaces Caladon integrates against:

  Letta (formerly MemGPT) .................................... Apache-2.0
      Agentic-memory backend. The gateway is a client-facing API in front of a
      separately-run Letta instance (proxied via httpx); Letta is not packaged
      here. https://github.com/letta-ai/letta

  RedPill / Phala attested inference ......................... (service / SDK)
      OpenAI-compatible attested (TDX + GPU-CC) inference endpoint used as a
      direct v1-chat backend. An external service, not bundled.
      https://red-pill.ai    https://phala.network

  litellm ................................................... MIT
      Listed in docs/oss-reuse-map.md as the planned in-CVM provider-abstraction
      layer. NOT a dependency of any manifest in this repository at this time.
      https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm

